The Green-phase note suggested introducing a per-scenario state object now, anticipating claim steps that reference policies by index. Deferred deliberately: no failing test demands it, and adding an abstraction ahead of need would violate Rule 4 (fewest elements) and YAGNI. When the first claim test goes red, the orchestrator can grow a `policies` array alongside `results` at that point — replacing the index-derived `isFollowUpContract` with `policies.length >= 1` will be a one-line follow-up.

